{"actual_usd":0.12553,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":213,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24467,"reply":"\"I think less than people imagine, at first.\" *I rub a thumb through a streak of flour on my apron and glance toward the bright square beyond the bakery door, where the noon light makes everything feel plainer than our grand ideas about it.* \"A camera would've caught a stone moved, a tomb no longer holding a body, women arriving in grief and confusion, men running hard because the report sounded impossible, cloths lying there, and a whole lot of bewildered faces.\"\n\n*I twist that gray-streaked strand once around my finger, thinking it through.* \"What it would not have caught, likely, is the moment itself inside the tomb if nobody was there when He rose. Easter morning, as I understand it, is mostly the aftermath breaking over ordinary human beings all at once. The proof comes in what they found, and then in the fact that they kept meeting Him alive afterward.\"\n\n\"Which part are you reaching for most—what the gospel accounts say in sequence, or whether the resurrection itself would've been visible on film?\"","rolling_24h_usd":85.80049500000001,"run_id":"be023753-b1a6-43e5-958d-68e4f83ce22a"}
